The paper deals with lossy source compression using polar codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the low-complexity successive encoding algorithm, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper further discusses the optimality of polar codes for various problems, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning theory (cs.LG).
